						<summary>

						<p>This is also mutilated like the above. It records the gift of lamp a called the <hi rend="italic">Īḻaviḷakku</hi> and of gold for burning the light (with the interest thereon) before god Vīdiviḍaṅgar during the service in the temple of Tāntōṉṟipperumāḷ at Vāḷaiyūr. The donor was a resident of Tañjāvūr by name Vēṭṭarai Kaviriyār. The amount is said to have been deposited with the <hi rend="italic">Nagarattār</hi> of the place.</p>						

						</summary>
